-- Rosatom Invites India to Jointly Mine Uranium in Siberia, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2010-11-22T05:16:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/rosatom-invites-india-to-mine-uranium-in-siberia-vedomosti-says.html
Rosatom Corp., Russian state-run
nuclear holding, invited Uranium Corp. of India Ltd. to jointly
develop a $3 billion Elkon uranium mine in East Siberia,
Vedomosti reported, citing Rosatom head Sergei Kirienko.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net . 